title.narrative: 603 STRENGTHENED FOR DECENTRALIZED PLANNING, IMPLEMENTATION AND MONITORING

description.narrative: Institutional capacities of governments at state level strengthened for decentralized planning, implementation, monitoring and using feedback in planning processes by 2022, which contributes to Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Social policies and strategies inform more effective and efficient planning, budgeting and implementation of social service programmes for reducing inequities and gender inequalities especially for the most vulnerable and marginalized children and adolescents by 2022

title.narrative: Institutional capacities of governments at state level strengthened for decentralized planning, implementation, monitoring and using feedback in planning processes by 2022

description.narrative: UNICEF's advocacy and technical support to Rural Development and Panchayati Raj department in the UNICEF programming states has led to creation of favorable eco-system for child friendly GPDP, leading to progress in capacity building of the district/block/village level functionaries and community members, strengthening institutional capacity, detailed guidelines for functioning of the CF-GPDP and institutionalization of Child, Young people and Women participation. UNICEF support has led to improvement of national SDG indicators and development of the State SDG Indicator Framework, embedding child centric global indicators. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:10/01/2020

title.narrative: Number of states that have functional monitoring system to monitor allocations, expenditures at Panchayat level with specific reference to adolescents, women, and children and marginalized

actual.value: 2019:Extensive progress made in the Child-Friendly Gram Panchayat Development Plan (GPDP) where most states have been able to strengthening the System by building capacity of the elected members, developing guidelines and development of indicators for measuring progress at state level.

title.narrative: National and UNICEF supported States Governments have capacity for SDGs monitoring.

actual.value: 2019:National and State Governments have enthusiastically developed SDG indicator Frameork embedding child centric indicators. Efforts are on to align it to the Global framework. National Govt developed its baseline report and disseminated it. States are working towards developing state specific dashboar
